Date: 24/11/1847
Source: Letters to His Father, 1843-1851
Author: H S CHAPMAN
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: Of course in these [bush] whares there are degrees of comfort and accommodation. In one tea is boiled in the kettle and drunk out of a pannikin: in another the tea is <i>made </i>in a tin teapot and drunk out of crockery.
Notes: 1847 Nov 24 H.S. Chapman Letters to His Father [TS, ATB] in 1958 Miller Early Victorian NZ 140

